column5: Hey gang,  Down in FLA for a few weeks. We got lucky and had Tropical Storm Fay swerve right around the Tampa area. The rest of the state is getting bombarded with rain and floods.  Anyways, I did manage to get some deep sea fishing in last weekend. Caught a red grouper, black grouper, 2 mangrove snapper, and a ton of grey snapper. See pics.  All fish were caught and devoured.
that brown one looks like you had a smallmouth in your cooler  anyways. nice stuff
What a tasty looking bunch of fish just waiting to go in the grease.
probably like moth balls and ointment what ,...never tasted grey snapper before????
brown one = yummy grouper fried crisp outside or steamed just oh so right   nice fish!
Great report and pics bassman  Nice looking bunch of groups Thanks for sharing Leechman
Something tells me you need to change your batter recipe Jack...
